  "prompt": "How fast can helicopters travel?",
  "response": "The speed of a helicopter can vary significantly depending on the model and design. Generally, most helicopters have a cruise speed ranging from about 100 to 160 knots (approximately 115 to 185 miles per hour or 185 to 300 kilometers per hour). \n\nSome high-performance models, such as the Sikorsky S-76, can reach speeds of around 155 knots (about 178 mph or 286 km/h), while military helicopters like the Boeing AH-64 Apache can achieve speeds of about 140 knots (around 161 mph or 259 km/h). \n\nHowever, certain specialized helicopters can reach higher speeds. The fastest helicopter, as of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, is the Eurocopter X3, which achieved a speed of 255 knots (around 292 mph or 470 km/h) in level flight during testing.\n\nIt's essential to note that speed can also be affected by factors such as weight, altitude, and weather conditions.",
